SAGEWOOD OFFERS CLIENTS AN OVERLAY STRATEGY THAT SEEKS TO GENERATE RETURNS BY EXPLOITING PERCEIVED INEFFICIENCIES IN THE PRICING OF EQUITY MARKET VOLATILITY. THE STRATEGY UTILIZES A DISCIPLINED QUANTITATIVE INVESTMENT PROCESS COMBINED WITH THOROUGH QUALITATIVE ANALYSIS TO MANAGE A PORTFOLIO OF OPTIONS.  THE STRATEGY IS OFFERED ON A DISCRETIONARY BASIS AND IS GENERALLY IMPLEMENTED AS AN OVERLAY ON A CLIENT'S EXISTING ASSET ALLOCATION.  THEREFORE, INVESTMENTS MADE PURSUANT TO THIS PROGRAM ARE GENERALLY COLLATERALIZED USING MARGIN AND CLIENTS ARE REQUIRED TO DESIGNATE ONE OR MORE ACCOUNTS WHOSE ASSETS SERVE AS COLLATERAL (THE "COLLATERAL ACCOUNTS").  WE GENERALLY DO NOT TAILOR ADVISORY SERVICES TO INDIVIDUAL NEEDS OF THE CLIENTS.

SOME OF OUR CLIENT PORTFOLIOS ARE ESTABLISHED WITH THE CUSTODIAN AS MARGIN ACCOUNTS. MARGIN IS RARELY USED BY OUR CLIENTS. WIC DOES NOT USE MARGIN AS PART OF OUR INVESTMENT STRATEGIES. AS OF THE DATE OF THIS FILING, THERE WERE NO BORROWINGS OR MARGIN BALANCE ON PORTFOLIOS VALUED OVER $10,000,000.  THE USE OF DERIVATIVES IS ONLY THROUGH WRITING COVERED CALLS ON EQUITY POSITIONS.  THIS INVESTMENT STRATEGY IS PART OF THE WIC MANAGED VOLATILITY AND INCOME STRATEGY (MVIS).  MVIS INVESTS IN A DIVERSIFIED PORTFOLIO OF U.S. TRADED COMMON EQUITIES WITH COVERED CALL OPTIONS WRITTEN AGAINST 90% OR MORE OF THE UNDERLYING EQUITY POSITIONS.
